# Extending Exception

You can create your own exception classes by extending `Exception`. This allows you to define custom exception types for different error categories.

```php
class ValidationException extends Exception {}
class DatabaseException extends Exception {}

// Then throw specific exceptions
if (!$valid) {
    throw new ValidationException('Invalid input');
}
```

You can add your own methods to custom exceptions.

```php
<?php
class InsufficientFundsException extends Exception {
    protected $balance;

    public function __construct($message, $balance, $code = 0) {
        parent::__construct($message, $code);
        $this->balance = $balance;
    }

    public function getBalance() {
        return $this->balance;
    }
}

class BankAccount {
    private $balance = 0;

    public function withdraw($amount) {
        if ($amount > $this->balance) {
            throw new InsufficientFundsException("Insufficient funds", $this->balance);
        }
        $this->balance -= $amount;
    }
}
?>
```
